Debt Capital Markets

Partner with one of the world leaders in fixed income.
Cantor Debt Capital Markets (DCM), launched in 2003, has leveraged the firm’s solid roots in bond brokerage to become a world-class dealer, positioning billions of dollars in inventory across a broad spectrum of fixed income products. Our dedicated team of more than 200 sales and trading professionals offers unparalleled personal commitment and our state-of-the-art electronic trading platform provides superior liquidity and transaction execution.
Cantor DCM provides sales, trading and other institutional services on a principal basis to more than 5,000 customers worldwide. As our partner, we will work closely with you to execute strategies - from yield enhancement and leveraging solutions to hedging and risk management.  We also offer services such as Market Technical Analysis, Asset/Liability Management, and Balance Sheet Analysis to meet our clients overall investment requirements and objectives.










Credit Securities
Trading ideas for a broad array of fixed income instruments











Structured Products
New issue securitizations and value creation through customized structures













Asset-Backed & Mortgage-Backed Securities
Sales and trading of Treasuries, agencies, corporates, mortgages, and repurchase agreements











Emerging Market Credit Securities
Trading sovereign and corporate debt from emerging economies













US Government Agency Securities
Creation, trading and distribution in agency debt











US Treasury Securities & Interest Rate Products
Primary dealer in all US government securities













Whole Loans
Creating opportunity across residential, commercial, and multi-family sectors








 







