Cantor Fitzgerald L.P. is a global financial services firm specializing in bond trading, investment banking, asset management, market data and brokerage services. Its subsidiaries Cithaeron Partners LLC, CantorCO2e, Cantor Entertainment, Cantor Fitzgerald Telecom Services, LLC, Cantor Market Data, Cantor Equity… MoreCantor Fitzgerald L.P. is a global financial services firm specializing in bond trading, investment banking, asset management, market data and brokerage services. Its subsidiaries Cithaeron Partners LLC, CantorCO2e, Cantor Entertainment, Cantor Fitzgerald Telecom Services, LLC, Cantor Market Data, Cantor Equity Research, Cantor Fitzgerald Spectrum & Tower Exchange & Marketplace, Cantor Gaming, Helix Financial Systems, Cantor Exchange, and Cantor Index Ltd.
Cantor Fitzgerald L.P. is a global financial services firm specializing in bond trading, investment banking, asset management, market data and brokerage services. Its subsidiaries Cithaeron Partners LLC, CantorCO2e, Cantor Entertainment, Cantor Fitzgerald Telecom Services, LLC, Cantor Market Data, Cantor Equity… MoreCantor Fitzgerald L.P. is a global financial services firm specializing in bond trading, investment banking, asset management, market data and brokerage services. Its subsidiaries Cithaeron Partners LLC, CantorCO2e, Cantor Entertainment, Cantor Fitzgerald Telecom Services, LLC, Cantor Market Data, Cantor Equity Research, Cantor Fitzgerald Spectrum & Tower Exchange & Marketplace, Cantor Gaming, Helix Financial Systems, Cantor Exchange, and Cantor Index Ltd. 

Cantor Fitzgerald, L.P. is based in New York, NY, though the company's IT personnel are spread through its various offices. Cantor Fitzgerald has two chief information officers who lead their respective IT departments and integrate the strategic direction of the department with the company's business goals.

Teams at Debt Capital Markets focus on architecture and wireless technology. A group oversees Human Capital Management which is based on Oracle and PeopleSoft. A development team also oversees software initiatives for Cantor. 
Prominent company technologies include CA Cybermation ESP, Oracle Applications (EBS, Advanced Procurement, HCM, and iProcurement), Microsoft Products, PeopleSoft, Sybase RAP, TIBCO, EMC PowerPath, Sybase, Palo Alto Networks, Linux, Sun Solaris, UNIX, and Wintel Servers.

Cantor Fitzgerald, L.P. has previously focused on the areas of data protection and recovery software. Its top storage pain points are data security, data loss, and compliance issues. Cantor Fitzgerald, L.P. uses disk backup across NAS, SAN, and DAS environment to back up its hybrid of block and file data.  

 Its daily and weekly total data backup is 30TB and 300TB respectively, with a >8 hours backup window.  Its backup growth is around 10.  There is a standard process for bringing on new sites and doing backup and disaster recovery in new locations.

 The IT budget is typically finalized in Q3.

IT Intelligence Snippets



•1-5 pb data volume company-wide across 6 to 10 data centers, and expects an annual data growth of 11-20%. 
•50-74% of its servers are to be virtualized by the end of 2013.
•Corporate IT manages 500 mobile devices.
•Corporate IT manages 2000 desktops. 
•Data center strategy is centered on whatever is best for applications – VMs/standalone server/custom hardware appliance, and minimizing cost. 
•Long term plan for running new applications is to add servers and virtualize, but no new facilities are scheduled.





